    <item>
      <title>14.11 The Safflower (3)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-11-the-safflower-3/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-11-the-safflower-3/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 30 Nov 2024 12:59:50 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.11 The Safflower&amp;nbsp;(3)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-10-the-safflower-2/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The next day, Maomao headed to Hao’s residence as soon as she finished her work as a court physician assistant.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Instead of Hao who was absent, perhaps as Jinshi wasn’t here today, it was the lady who courteously came to greet them at the door. There were also a few servants, but the concubine in question was nowhere in sight.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I hear you know who is the culprit,” the lady said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. We would like to give a detailed explanation, but may we change locations?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Mamei took charge. Although Chue also came along, it was better to leave it to Mamei.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady looked unwell, same as yesterday.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Come this way.” The lady guided Maomao and the others to the parlour.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady, an attendant, and Maomao’s group of three entered the large room. A guard stood watch by the door outside.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So you know the truth about the curse jar, right?” The lady&amp;#8217;s red nose dipped slightly. It seems she was deliberately asking them while knowing the answer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Mamei looked at Maomao.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao opened her mouth. “It is not a curse jar but a poison one. A substance that, in the guise of an illness, will gradually weaken the person until they succumb. The poison was created from ingredients within reach, and was in the process of aging under the ground.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Such a thing was buried under the eaves, I see.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;So fake,&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought. She thought, but given the lady’s position, that was the only thing she could do. “Yes. It was made by Hao-sama’s concubine. And her daughter was the one she poisoned.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;” The lady continued to hang her head. She didn’t look shocked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;So she really did know, huh?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The one who had exchanged letters with the empress dowager hadn’t been the family head but the lady. What kind of objective did the lady have to go out of her way to ask the empress dowager for advice on the curse jar? And the empress dowager, being who she is, had taken the trouble to send Jinshi over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The daughter’s name is Zhizi. Was she given the name of a flower related to the family?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s right. Thanks to that, I am called Suetsumuhana,” the lady said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Suetsumuhana.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Suetsumuhana is the other name for safflower. The lady touched her red-dyed nose. That alone allowed Maomao to presume that was the reason the woman was called the other name for safflower.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“To think that it’s not Zhizi-san’s mother, but the lady who is called Suetsumuhana,” Maomao said, slightly astonished.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Balsam and wood sorrel.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She recalled the names that were once given on a whim. “Was it to seem like mother and child even if there is no blood relation?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;No, not like this either, huh?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She ended up saying her thoughts out loud. She thought it would sour the mood, but the lady was, surprisingly, taken aback. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wh-what are you saying?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I know right. What am I saying?” Maomao thought so herself too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“At least, you are a good person for not being able to abandon Zhizi-san even though you share no blood relation.” Maomao extended her hand towards Chue.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, yes, Maomao-san,” Chue said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Thank you, Chue-san.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue passed a bottle over. Maomao uncapped it and the scent of milk wafted out. “So you even milked the cows in the cowshed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. If not milked well, they get inflamed. More importantly, cow’s milk is nutritious and stimulates physical growth,” the lady said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You know a lot.”　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My family originally managed the cows of the inner palace. If I tell you that we had a history, but were reduced to poverty and got absorbed into another family as a result, would you understand?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So that was why she became Hao’s wife. Considering family history and her knowledge, the advantage to taking her as a wife had been great.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So you gave this nutritious milk to Zhizi-san.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Aside from symptoms of poisoning, Zhizi-san was showing signs of chronic malnutrition. I hear she is fourteen years of age, but she is much smaller than average. I hear she has been weak since young, but is that the truth?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It seems Zhizi-san’s meals are managed by the concubine. I had a short chat with all the cooks on my way to the cowshed, you seeee,” Chue cut in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Did you not consider that it was the mean legal wife who poisoned the concubine’s child?” the lady asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you had thought such a thing, then you probably wouldn’t have gone to the empress dowager about the curse jar. Although the family head is Hao-sama, there is no mistaking that the mistress of this household is you,” Maomao said bluntly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The lady’s reputation is really good among the servants. Myyy, what a good laaady,” Chue said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady let out a cynical laugh. “Hahaha. What an odd thing you say. My husband only tells me to not sit next to him at banquets, to show consideration for others from the background. Above of all else, he didn’t even introduce me yesterday either, did he?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. However, this household will not run if the lady wasn’t around.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems the previous family head had been a capable person, but the current one was uninspiring. Could the lady’s presence be what was somehow making things work out?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Normally, it wouldn’t be possible to act as the intermediary for the family head and the empress dowager when they didn’t get along. &lt;em&gt;The woman was that much cultured,&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And didn’t you also give birth to three sons? Myy, aren’t you the ideal bride for the family heaaad?” Chue said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady’s expression was yet gloomy. Her sense of inferiority towards her own looks was greater than anyone else.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Shall we return to the topic at hand? The lady would immediately deny it, so I will now just express my opinions. Whether I am right or wrong, you need not to respond,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady watched Maomao without moving. Although, it seems as though her complexion had improved slightly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao talked about the things she told Jinshi and the others yesterday. “She had used her daughter to evoke the family head’s compassion. However, the cat ended up finding the poison jar by chance.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady closed her eyes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“When did you start giving Zhizi-san cow’s milk? Lady, you need not say anything. I will know once I ask Zhizi-san.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady opened her mouth. “&amp;#8230;Please do not make children sell out their mothers. I gave that child cow’s milk before she turned ten. I had my sons and the servants do it for me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Did the person not do it herself because she was not fit to be seen?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My husband is moved by the the woman who weeps that her sickly daughter is pitiful. Yes, weak women, that’s what that person likes. He doesn’t understand that if you give a child nothing more than watery congee, they wouldn’t be any more different from a sick person. He gets told that because she’s sick that she gets congee, and he says nothing and nods, even buying expensive herbal medicines to gift her.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao leaned forwards, lips twitching, the moment she heard &lt;em&gt;herbal medicines&lt;/em&gt;, but Chue poked her, and she righted her posture.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady didn’t call the concubine by her name, but referred to her as &lt;em&gt;the woman&lt;/em&gt;. She had her opinions about the concubine. “That woman knows very well. She knows very well what my husband likes. In the past, my husband had repeatedly kept concubines, but in the end, that woman was the only one left. The other women were all driven out with consolation money. Perhaps the women who were called to the residence and kept here were truly more loved than I was. Right when I behaved like the legal wife, it resulted with my husband telling me that he was sick of my haughtiness.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Take responsibility to the end, oi.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If that was a pet, that was what you would say.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But it were a human, it would be considerably kind to simply give them consolation money. Perhaps, it could actually be the lady who gave the consolation money.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The delicate woman kept coming over as though the family head couldn’t lose interest in her. And then, she even used her own daughter.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. I wanted to believe she had no relation to me. The concubine’s child that is an eyesore, who has no blood relation to me either. But I saw it by chance. The skinny child had bent over to try to eat a frog that was hopping on the ground.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tree frogs are toxic so I advise against eating them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When the lady, who came from a good family even if it had fallen to ruin, saw the starved child try to eat a live frog that was hopping around, she must have received a great shock.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“By giving her cow’s milk in secret these few years, it seems like her condition has improved greatly. However, Zhizi’s condition worsened in the last couple of months.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She had wondered why, then discovered the poison jar. And that was when the lady realised that the concubine had given Zhizi some kind of poison.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why didn’t you inform Hao-sama of his daughter’s abuse?” Mamei must have her own views as a mother herself.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I did inform him. What did you think happened when I did? He asked me if &lt;em&gt;I&lt;/em&gt; was the one doing the tormenting. Yes, that’s right. My husband sees me as a woman jealous of a concubine that is younger and more beautiful. I pressed the woman about it many times too, but the guests saw and even unsavoury rumours came about.” The lady smiled drily.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Was it the concubine good at currying favour, or was Hao shallow? It mattered not.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hao would call the concubine to his sleeping chambers in place of the lady. The concubine would probably tell him about how the lady would torment her in a reserved and plausible manner while in bed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“One way or other, I am also one of the causes as to why Zhizi became this weak. I wanted to save that child.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Which was why she came to the empress dowager for advice.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao swirled the bottle of milk. “Zhizi-san is fortunate, isn’t she?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“In what way?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That the lady gave her cow’s milk for nutrition. And as a result, not only did she get nutrition, she also narrowly escaped death.” Maomao swirled the bottle, and it made a sloshing sound.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why do you mean by not only did she get nutritiooon?” Chue asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Cow’s milk does not interact well with tea. The milk loses all its nutritious value. To say it conversely, the toxin in tea is weakened when mixed with milk,” Maomao said.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Luomen had weakened the tea poison Maomao drank by giving her milk.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Considering the amount of poison, it wouldn’t be odd for her to be already dead. Considering how Zhizi was still alive, she must have narrowly escaped death due to the cow’s milk.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But as things stand, that is a chance that she would die if the poison isn’t completely counteracted.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How shocking. If she ended up dead, it would be for naught.” Mamei had a sense that there were personal feelings involved.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I guess so.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The weaker the daughter became, the more compassion the concubine received. She would do anything to become the leading actress of a tragedy.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What does the lady want the Moon Prince to do?”　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Did she want to tell Jinshi to do something about the concubine? Or…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can he take Zhizi into his care?” the lady asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Do you understand the implications of that?” Mamei asked without a moment’s delay.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Telling an imperial to take the daughter into his care could only be taken as telling him to marry her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. I understand how disrespectful it is. Even if he were to take her in as an attendant, Zhizi’s existence would have to be a hindrance. This child as of now doesn’t have the capacity nor the strength to work as an attendant.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, why did you bring up such a thing?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Zhizi cannot give birth to children. My husband had wondered if she truly couldn’t enter the inner palace. He had a doctor check up on her.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;” Mamei fell silent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The daughter of a powerful person was ultimately a piece for political marriages. Even Mamei who appeared free understood that fact.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“All of this is the result of this family’s misconduct,” the lady forced herself to say.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“To make amends for Zhizi-san, you want the Moon Prince to take her into custody. Mmmm, honestly, I don’t see there being any merit for the Moon Priiince.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was as Chue said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The Moon Prince visited Hao-sama’s residence. Then, he took his daughter into his care. To an onlooker, they would only see it as the Moon Prince, who has yet to have a concubine, having taken a liking to Hao-sama’s daughter and sought to marry her,” Mamei also said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;That’s how it’ll turn out, yeah.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hao would have to be overjoyed no matter the form. The imperial brother who lacked any juicy gossip had taken a liking to his daughter.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What does Maomao-san thiiink?” Chue whispered into Maomao’s ear as she elbowed her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good question.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Does Chue want to see Maomao jealous?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Unfortunately she didn’t think that way.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I think I would feel bad for Zhizi-san if she were to get any strange hopes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hm, in short, you’re implying that the Moon Prince won’t be drawn to other women, huuuh?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;You always have the last word.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao decided to say nothing more.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems the lady had expected the answer. She lightly nodded in agreement. “The empress dowager also told me the same thing. However, there is one advantage to it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What kind of advantage?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“She could be used as grounds to ward off the ever increasing annoying marriage talks from now on.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems as though Mamei and Chue’s ears grew.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahh, my word.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That might be appealing.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The two of them glanced at Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But the fact that she has a selfish mother is an issue.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I will not send that woman with her,” the lady declared. “I doubt my husband would compel even the concubine. That woman would surely object, but there is no way that she could go against it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was no way that a concubine Hao doted on could even weigh up against the imperial brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It is likely that the others would change the way they think about my husband, but that is all temporary. His footing isn’t as solid as the Gyoku family. Even if it increases the weight of my family a little, it shouldn’t make a large difference to the power dynamic.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nngh,” Mamei groaned. It seems the lady wasn’t entirely wrong.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I knew the lady is smart&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao though.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even so, there’s too little advantages to thiiiis,” Chue said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have three sons. I believe all of them are outstanding, but they have reserved personalities and will not forget gratitude. Besides, they don’t have the character to have wild ambitions like my husband does,” the lady said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What are you implying?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The family head may look young, but he is fifty-five this year. He might live for another decade, perhaps?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She was saying that the next family head will pledge his allegiance to Jinshi.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;So she isn’t a wife that only supports her husband, huh?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The lady had been far-sighted, confident that she would get the final triumph.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Which was why she continued to endure even in misfortune.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We cannot simply give you an answer,” Mamei said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the end, they left taking the answer back with them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-12-spell/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-11-the-safflower-3/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5113-6766daf98cc54' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241221#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5113&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5113-6766daf98cc54' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5113-6766daf98cc54' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-11-the-safflower-3/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
