    <item>
      <title>14.09 The Safflower (1)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-09-the-safflower-1/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-09-the-safflower-1/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 24 Nov 2024 08:50:16 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.09 The Safflower&amp;nbsp;(1)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: The chapter title is Suetsumuhana (末摘花). It is the archaic name of the safflower that is now known as benibana (紅花) in modern times. Fun fact: people who have read the Tale of Genji would recognise the archaic name of this flower to be the name of one of Genji&amp;#8217;s lovers, the Safflower Princess, who is known as one of his most loyal lovers, but with an unattractive nose that is described as &lt;strong&gt;red&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;We have two new character names:&lt;br&gt;&amp;#8211; 來, Lai (romaji reading is Rai, which is the Mandarin reading)&lt;br&gt;&amp;#8211; 梔子, Zhizi (romaji reading is Jiizuu, also the Mandarin reading)&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-08-the-curse-jar-2/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They decided to set out immediately as they were in a hurry. Although it was already dark out, the residence was located in the capital.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi began his explanation while in the carriage. He also included things Maomao had already heard as a recap for her, as forgetful as she is.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Mamei and Chue were on a different carriage, and Basen followed them on horseback. Needless to say, this was arranged by Chue.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, Maomao and Jinshi had completely switched to work-mode, so the development that Chue expected won’t come to pass.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The empress dowager has a complicated relationship with her family,” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The empress dowager was the daughter of the concubine of the former family head. The current head was her half-brother. He was called Hao, but Maomao reckoned she would forget his name in no time while she was listening to Jinshi talk.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They were a merchant family with beginnings dealing extensively with dyes. Around a century ago they supplied to the imperial court and it was through this connection that the men of the clan had become government officials. It seems that ochre, the forbidden colour, was also produced by the empress dowager’s family.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They were upstarts in a sense, but in time, that became history. During the era of the late emperor, they were properly treated as a mid-level family.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They also sold garments, and it was with this link they got involved with work related to the inner palace. It must be this information network they tapped into that had them later sending in the young Anshi who gave birth to the reigning emperor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In current times, they should be a family that had found a solid position, however…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The empress regnant was vigilant of the previous family head. They were never bestowed a clan name despite their association as the imperial family’s maternal relative.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I see,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In short, they were not a named clan.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The current family head Hao isn’t on good terms with the empress dowager. If anything, they’re on bad terms. It seems she does not exchange letters with Hao directly, but frequently with the lady.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I see.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Under normal circumstance, they would be family that could act more importantly, but there was a reason why they couldn’t exercise as much influence as expected.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;But they still have enough power to stir up the imperial court.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If they are on bad terms, wouldn’t the empress dowager also have the choice to not take an interest in this matter?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Don’t say that. If she continued to feign ignorance, the victims would be the concubine’s child and her mother. Isn’t it really similar to her own situation?” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If she remembered correctly, the empress dowager was also the child of a concubine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even if she told you to save her, there are limits. If it were a false charge, then that would be a different story, but in the case where she clearly has an intent to kill, then there is nothing I can do for her,” Maomao said.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Honestly, the girl was the most suspicious as the suspect.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“In that case, it can’t be helped. We only want to know the truth. You can just go confirm that.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It would be nice if we can figure that out simply. By the way, what kind of role should I take up?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Right, yeah.&amp;nbsp; I just told them you are knowledgeable in insect poisons, but well, I think it would be pointless to hide it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also, you may hate this, but honestly speaking, it’s handy to throw the tactician’s name around.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m aware.” She was very much aware.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What a pain&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought as she looked outside.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The residence was located at a distance that didn’t need a carriage. Annoyingly, it wasn’t far from the weirdo tactician’s residence.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The capital may be large, but it was limited by living spaces. It was inevitable that the residences of high officials would be in the same area. It was also influenced by the land, so it was easier for estates constructed later to be smaller than others.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hao’s residence that they were brought to was by no means small. However, it was much too ordinary for a one with the status of the empress dowager’s family.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The gate had a family crest that was a combination of safflower and gardenia.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Both flowers were used as herbal medicines, but they were better known as dyes. Ochre was a yellow tinged with red, so it was created from a mixture of red from the safflower and yellow from the gardenia.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Though imperfect, it was the imperial brother’s visit, so there was a group lined up to greet him at the gate.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;They did say that’s he’s of patrilineal descent.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There were certainly no young maidens around. If there were, they were clearly dressed as servants. Let’s leave out how the women were looking at Jinshi.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was a skinny woman in her fifties. Despite her pale complexion, only her nose was painted with scarlet rouge. This woman was the best dressed, so she had to be the lady.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was also a beauty in her mid-thirties. She was standing at the back humbly, but her dress was the next finest after the lady’s. It was remarkably refined for a servant.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Pardon us that it is late at night.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The person who spoke to Jinshi was a man in his forties or fifties. He had to the most important person based on his attire and where he stood, so she could tell he was Hao, the current family head. Although, she could sense that he was lacking in a dignified air. Could the reason be his youthful features? He might look a few years older if he had grown a beard, but he didn’t grow one, perhaps due to thin body hair.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is where I can sense his blood relation with the empress dowager.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The empress dowager was also a baby face.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, my apologies instead. By all rights, we should have settled this matter privately, and yet we have caused trouble to people. Gosh, Anshi has always been a worrier since way back.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hao spoke like he got along with the empress dowager. The person must want to be seen in a favourable light.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Let’s head inside for now. It’s cold, so I have prepared a warm meal.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We have already eaten dinner. Rather than that, let’s resolve this issue quickly,” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hao’s face twisted for an instant.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao recognised this person to be easy to understand, for better or worse. The previous generation’s family head who had sent the empress dowager into the inner palace was most likely to have had a sharp mind. However, she saw nothing of that razor sharpness in the son. Otherwise, he wouldn’t assume such a carefree attitude towards the imperial brother’s personal visit to his residence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;His parents raised him wrong.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She heard of the saying where one generation of wealth will be gone by the third generation, but could she take this guy as an example of that?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Gyoku clan of the west she saw recently appeared similar, but they still had a lot of outstanding sons and daughters.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hao glanced at Maomao and shot her a look of displeasure, but he didn’t make any further reaction. As Jinshi told her, for better or worse, she could use the weirdo tactician talisman as people repellent.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, I would guide you inside, but there is a sick person in the building, so how about the Moon Prince wait here?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What did you say when the cursed jar was brought over?” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That was Anshi’s doing.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Alrighty.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought the man called Hao also had a strength. Despite his young features, he was quite thick-skinned. She could tell by looking at him that he would later cover up the word curse and only spread around the news that the imperial brother had visited his household.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;She needn’t purposely dispatch Jinshi then,&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Guide them courteously.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Perhaps Hao didn’t want to get close to the place that was said to be cursed, he brought a different guide. The guide was a young man in his mid-twenties, much younger than Hao. Considering his baby-faced genes, he might be older than he looked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My name is Lai. I will guide you on behalf of my father.” The son behaved like he was aware of his position to some extent. It didn’t look like he had any intention of showing himself off.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I’m gonna forget his name…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please make an effort to remember names when you’re here at leaaast,” Chue whispered into her ear. She saw through Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With her usual habit, Maomao ended up studying the inside of the residence. It was hard to see under the moonlight, but she suddenly caught a whiff of a pungent stench.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It smells of a field.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao sniffed the air and looked towards where the smell was coming from. There was an impressive cow shed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What could that beee?” Chue asked for Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It is a cowshed. The previous emperor bestowed us cows that were used for transport in the inner palace. We are at the third generation,” Lai said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The current emperor didn’t use oxcarts as they were too slow. Maomao won’t say that he had been discreetly pushed onto one.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Afterwards, Lai barely spoke. Normally, people would introduce their prided garden or talk about their family’s history. It might be because it was so dark they couldn’t see so there was nothing to talk about, but even so, it was quiet. Chue was restless, wanting to chat, but Mamei elbowed her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The father was a pushy person, but the son only spoke when spoken to. Although his looks resembled his father, was his personality more like the lady?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao appreciated it, but she got worried that everyone would eat him up if he were to become Hao’s successor. Or could he have other siblings?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It’s hard to be in the middle.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While thinking of arbitrary things like how a family is ruined by the third generation, they arrived at their destination.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“This is the place.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Lai guided them to under the eaves. He directed his light over to make it easier to see. To the north, there was a muddy section where the colour of the soil was different as though a hole about one &lt;em&gt;shaku&lt;sub&gt;(30cm) &lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/em&gt;wide had been dug up. There was also a rectangular mark around it, so it looked like there was something placed on top of it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The jar was here.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao looked at Jinshi. Jinshi waved his palm, gesturing for the man to speak freely. “Was it buried in the ground?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, the jar was buried. The shelf over there had been on top of it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The shelf had been moved a short distance away. It was for outdoor use; gardening tools were stored in it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;They should borrow digging tools from there.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was muddy under the eaves of the detached building. People didn’t seem to come here normally. And if there were, would it only be the gardener to store their tools?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How was it found?” Jinshi asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“By chance. The cat was covered to mud, so I went to see what it did and I found a hole dug out here,” Lai said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It was a cat?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. The cat is left in the care of my family since my cousin’s daughter entered the inner palace.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If people were aware of even the gardener’s movements, it was possible that the jar could be buried by anyone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have heard that someone lives in this detached building. Is it possible for me to meet them?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;My younger sister lives here. She is sickly and much younger than me. She is fifteen years old. A smart child, but she eats very little and rarely goes outside.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can I examine her condition once?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Lai glanced at Jinshi.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why not? Let her.” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood.” There was no way he could turn down a proposal from the imperial family.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I will wait here. It wouldn’t be good for a man to enter a woman’s room.” Jinshi came to a stop at the front of the room. This was a consideration from what women regarded as a fine man. The reality was that it would be troublesome if he were to show his face and they fall for him–it was a reason typical of Jinshi.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Yeah, that’ll be nothing but unpleasant.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, please wait in the room next door.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi waited in the room next door. Maomao had Chue accompanying her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We’re coming in.” Lai opened the door. There were two women inside.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;One was a girl who had a pale complexion. She still had a childish innocence in her features.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The other person was the beauty in her thirties, one of the people who greeted them at the gate just now.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;So she’s actually the concubine.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The mother and daughter pair looked similar. If she wasn’t sickly, Hao would have pushed his daughter into the inner palace.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The room was dark. When a candle was lit, it even looked like there were white faces floating.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Perhaps due to the scarce visual information, Maomao’s nose reacted much more sensitively. She caught the smell of honey from the candle, and the smell of medicinal broth from the small teapot. Did it contain components that induced sleep?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Also, she felt a sense of nostalgia from the beauty.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;She must have been from the pleasure district and got redeemed.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Her outfit was simple, but her air and the way she dressed herself wasn’t something that could be readily changed. She possessed a sensuality that brought to mind a courtesan’s figure in a dim bedroom. There was no expressed need for Maomao to point that out, so she kept silent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The Moon Prince’s company wishes to see Zhizi,” Lai said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Zhizi!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a superb name. Zhizi was gardenia, which was used as a dye, but also as a herbal medicine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;That said, I wonder if they will give me anything as a souvenir.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She was fine with either safflower or gardenia.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Who is this person?” The beautiful concubine studied Maomao intently.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“She is the herbalist approved by the imperial brother. Do you have any doooubts?” Chue threatened her with a smile.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nonsense. However, this child has been visited by many a doctor and she has yet to be cured…” The concubine hugged her daughter gently as she sobbed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The daughter with lifeless eyes clutched her mother’s arms.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please allow me to examine her regardless.” Maomao took Zhizi’s hand. She took the girl’s pulse, and even checked her eyes and tongue.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When she checked Zhizi’s tongue, she detected a faint smell of milk from the girl.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Excuse me, but can I have a cup of tea?” Maomao pointed at the small teapot where the smell of medicinal broth came from.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then I will brew it again.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, it is fine as it is. It has a very pleasant smell with a good sleep effect.” Maomao sniffed the air.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, these are used up. I will boil up some water and prepare a fresh serving.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Thank you.” Maomao accepted the medicinal broth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I knew it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She downed the teacup in one go.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I will prepare the medicine for the daughter’s condition, so may I come over on another day?” Maomao said, looking at Lai.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That is welcome news for me, but…. Um…” Lai looked at the concubine and her daughter.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems the main question was if it was the curse jar.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I think I will talk about that matter on another day,” Maomao said as she swirled the tea leaves left in the bottom of the teacup.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: The lady&amp;#8217;s red nose is probably a reference to the Genji character.&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;Also, in case it wasn&amp;#8217;t clear, the comment Maomao made about Jinshi being of patrilineal descent, that&amp;#8217;s referring to how he&amp;#8217;s an imperial with inheritance rights.&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-10-the-safflower-2/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-09-the-safflower-1/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5064-6767064c7c1a5' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241221#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5064&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5064-6767064c7c1a5' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5064-6767064c7c1a5' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-09-the-safflower-1/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
