    <item>
      <title>14.10 The Safflower (2)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-10-the-safflower-2/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-10-the-safflower-2/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Nov 2024 12:09:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.10 The Safflower&amp;nbsp;(2)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-09-the-safflower-1/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao and the others decided to leave Hao’s residence for now.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Unlike the journey to, the carriage was cramped. The reason was Mamei and Chue’s presence.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They could probably squeeze in one more person, but Basen wasn’t useful, so they left him out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As it was already late at night, they decided to share information on their way back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Now then, how about you give us a recount on what you’ve noticed?” Jinshi, arms crossed, asked Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It will be speculation like always,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Give us speculation like always.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought about how she should broach it, then decided to speak frankly as she had nothing to hide. “The concubine was the one who made the poison, and the daughter was the one who was served the poison.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, you spoke so directly. How unusuaaal.” Chue was rocking herself in time with the carriage.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The mother to the daughter, is that right?” Mamei confirmed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Not every mother has maternal feelings, you knooow.” Chue said what Maomao wanted to say.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you certain that she served the poison?” Jinshi asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I cannot declare it outright, but in all possibility, I believe it to be the case.” Maomao presented her basis, “The tea I had just now contained several medicinal herbs. It had a sleep-inducing effect, and didn’t taste bad either&amp;#8230;but it’s likely to be the very tea brewed for the poison in question.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If Basen were here, he would be squawking. Unfortunately he wasn’t. Jinshi, used to it, was composed with his arms crossed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Seeing as you’re not all that excited, it doesn’t seem like you have ingested poison,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Just as the Moon Prince said. The concubine brewed up a fresh batch instead of the used up tea for heeer,” Chue said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And even if it were ingested, it would not bring out abnormalities to your body as long as you do not take it everyday,” Maomao added. It was ultimately a slow-acting poison. “And the daughter Zhizi-san’s condition has the same symptoms as taking the poison too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao looked at Jinshi and Mamei. They looked bewildered. Chue had been with Maomao in that room, so it seems like she was deep into the role of filling in the lacking sections of Maomao’s testimony.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao remembered the name of a stranger after hearing it once…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;That’s what you’re focused on?!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even Maomao has remembered names she heard once. Like Wanwan-senpai.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why would the mother poison her daughter? Just the reasoning that she didn’t give out the used up tea is too weak.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was just as Mamei said. Maomao thought so too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“As far as I could tell, she didn’t seem like a mother who thought of her daughter. As far as I could teeell.” Chue had some misgivings about the mother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The fresh tea she brewed for me was a little bitter. Also, it had catnip,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Catnip?” Jinshi asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. There is cat in its name. Its use is close to silver vine. The herb is used as herbal medicine, but just like silver vine, it’s liked by cats.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Speaking of cats…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Back when she was at the inner palace, there was a detestable calico cat by the name of Maomao that had always gone after the silver vine in the medical office.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If people touch catnip often, the smell might get on them.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Which was why the cat found the poison jar.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But Zhizi-san’s mother didn’t have a reason to harm her daughter. It’ll make more sense if it were the legal wife instead.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;According to advance information, the mother and daughter were neglected.&amp;nbsp; Let alone entering the inner palace, the daughter was forced into a detached building without coming out in public.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“To my eyes, the mother and daughter did not look close.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahhh, does Maomao-san think so tooo?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. That person was less a &lt;em&gt;mother &lt;/em&gt;and more a &lt;em&gt;woman &lt;/em&gt;to me,” Maomao said bluntly. That was the reason she identified the concubine to be a former courtesan.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The reason Chue had misgivings.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;First class courtesans operate by luring in customers. Everything they do is calculated, from the angle they tilt their head to make them look pretty to customers, the flow of their hair, to the movement of their fingers.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The concubine had moved to make herself look the most pitiful to Maomao and the others, the guests. Movements that were very much like the skilled courtesans at the Verdigris Mansion who made themselves look delicate.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So you mean she was arousing sympathy?” Jinshi asked back, looking like he couldn’t understand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. The concubine and her daughter hadn’t been treated as roughly as our prior information told us. If anything, I think they were treated really well.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The concubine’s attire was the next-most splendid after the lady’s. If she had been neglected, she wouldn’t be allowed to show her face at the imperial brother’s greeting in the first place.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Same with the daughter. If she had an unknown disease that even doctors have given up on, it would be natural to have her live separately from the main house. I would do the same as it would be scary if it turned out to be infectious. Even the tea she was given had various kinds of herbal medicines. It could not have been cheap.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Above all, the poison in the jar was made from high-grade tea leaves.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But the bad rumours…” Jinshi said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Honestly, it’s Hao-sama’s wife who did not look well. Suppose there is a concubine who is many years younger and more beautiful around, what would you think? And suppose that concubine, who is a kind mother who thinks of a daughter, is going around looking sorrowful, what would happen?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;People like to create convenient stories. Apart from the servants who were always in the residence, the guests would probably make up their own stories.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It is fine if all of it was just to make herself look delicate, but it is not acceptable to use her daughter as a prop.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“By prop, you don’t mean that she continued to poison her daughter to beget sympathy from other?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I believe that is the most valid reason for the poisoning.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No way.” Jinshi couldn’t believe it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;The senior courtesans are jealous of me. Look at the harm I suffered&lt;/em&gt;—there are courtesans who would show their purposely roughly cut hair to customers. Although, it was all done by themselves. This is an extension of that act. She used her daughter to her own advantage and wept to her husband. And her husband would end up feeling compassion for the pitiful woman.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But the advantage to weakening her daughter by poisoning is too small. Hao-dono has no other daughters. Wouldn’t it be wiser to have her enter the inner palace to become a consort?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Jinshi-sama, can you easily have a concubine’s… a former courtesan’s daughter become a high-ranking consort?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“…” Jinshi couldn’t say anything.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Since they controlled the inner palace, the selection of a high-ranking consort was made up of a number of factors.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“With all due respect, didn’t you get a lot of opposition when you promoted Empress Gyokuyou to high-ranking consort?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Empress Gyokuyou’s mother was one of the many wives of Gyoku&amp;#8217;en who governed the lands of the west. She was also mixed with western blood, so even now, there were a lot of voices questioning her suitability to be empress.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I do not know Hao-sama well, but wouldn&amp;#8217;t he pretend there was no courtesan mother to raise the chance of his daughter becoming a high-ranking consort?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The daughter was treated as the child of the legal wife instead of the concubine, which was why she was treated as if she didn’t exist. It was better to erase the existence of the courtesan who was in the background. It was better to have the daughter learn the skills of luring in men from her mother, and should she prove useful, have her become the adopted daughter of the legal wife. She could be registered as the legal wife’s daughter in the family register from the very start.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;And…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Once the daughter entered the inner palace, the courtesan would have served her purpose.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But what if the daughter couldn’t enter the inner palace due to poor health?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had no idea about the personality of the man called Hao. However, even supposing he wasn’t a person with deep feelings, he shouldn’t be callous enough to give up on his own daughter. Although not to the level of having her come out in public on a brilliant stage, he wouldn’t abandon her to starve to death.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Let’s say the concubine was looking for a way to not get abandoned by her husband. If she aroused sympathy from those around her, acted like a devoted mother, and occasionally get compared with the legal wife who is neither young nor beautiful, wouldn’t she regain a degree of self-respect?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Neither Jinshi nor Mamei look like they could believe it. Only Chue was grinning ominously.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Did she think it was the only way for her to live?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Nonetheless, Maomao herself found it really selfish.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It’s not a strong poison.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But definitely one that will destroy the body.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, it will be fine if we collect the evidence to confirm that fact tomorrow, riiight?” Chue, who seemed to be really good at gathering evidence, said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. There is also one place I want investigated,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Where would that beee?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I want you to investigate the cowshed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The cowshed?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Not only Chue, both Jinshi and Mamei also tilted their heads.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: Catnip in Japanese is 荊芥. Read as inuhakke. There is a line that said that there is dog (inu) in the name, but as you can see, it doesn&amp;#8217;t work in English, so I changed it to cat. &lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-11-the-safflower-3/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-10-the-safflower-2/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5096-6767064c9073b' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241221#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5096&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5096-6767064c9073b' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5096-6767064c9073b' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-10-the-safflower-2/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
