    <item>
      <title>14.01 Chicken Meat</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-01-chicken-meat/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-01-chicken-meat/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 12:01:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.01 Chicken Meat&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: New arc. Smallpox arc. Looks like the long wait is going to be worth it.&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;Wanwan is actually Wang Wang (王旺), but I feel the former works better in this case. Also sounds like woof woof, so I&amp;#8217;ll be keeping the Japanese reading for his name.&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/13-16-the-imperial-prince-and-his-wet-nurse/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Half a month after the emperor’s operation finished with no mishap, Maomao settled back into a workflow that consisted of half her usual work and half dosage experiments. A high-ranking court physician had taken over the emperor’s post-operative treatment. Although the scale of the dosage experiments have been reduced, the fact that they were keeping on with it was probably in the anticipation that it would prove useful here on after.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With the seasons getting colder, she also changed her medical robes to something thicker. The bedding for the patients in the town clinic would be supplemented with something a little thicker too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wanwan-senpai, are the medicines for restocking okay here?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao passed the account book to the tall senior, otherwise known as Wanwan-senpai.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s fine. For some reason I feel like you’ve been excessively calling me by my name lately.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also, I feel like the way you’re pronouncing it is a little peculiar.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Could it be your imagination?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Wanwan. Written as Wang Wang.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a name that Maomao, who was bad at remembering names, was super thankful for. It can’t be helped she pronounced it with fondness in her tone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Alright, now place the order of medicine for me,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood. Also, I will be returning to the imperial court this afternoon. Is there anything you want me to take care of?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Mmm. Nothing for now. Now that you mention it, you’re checking the medicine room today, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Wanwan-senpai checked the medicine stock inventory as Maomao did, so he knew whose turn it was.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, if Tianyu is in the area, get a rise out of him for me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“For sure.” Maomao replied, head held high.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tianyu was the one who made the biggest mess during the emperor’s surgery, which had been a terrible challenge. It would have been fine if his blunder was from extreme stress, but in his case, it was for his personal reasons, so he had no grounds for extenuating circumstances. Tianyu was the one at fault for bringing personal interest into a job that concerned the life of the emperor. Rather, the fact that he didn’t lose his head over this was an act of clemency.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He received quite the pay cut, but the remainder was a freeloader&amp;#8217;s food expenses, so you could say that he was unpaid.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And so, Tianyu will be working without pay for the time being. Not only that, he was now punished with every single court physician out to drive him crazy.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even if they did get a rise from him, Tianyu was aloof by nature. Getting Tianyu to feel vexed became the biggest thing among the court physicians.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Whether it would be called bullying or not…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Far from getting discouraged, the person himself was even having a great time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And so, Maomao returned to the imperial court.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Her junior Yo was in the medicine room. She would replenish the stock when Maomao and the others were away.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, I just replenished the stock, so check, please.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Okay.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The clever junior diligently learnt the fundamentals. Furthermore, she wasn’t conceited and would wash the bandages and sheets and disinfect the tools.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It’s wonderful that she does the fundamentals properly.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;No matter how clever they were, if they don’t listen to people, they were of bad character. And then a person of bad character showed up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hey, Niangniang and Yo. In the middle of work?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was Tianyu.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought about ignoring him, but she remembered what Wanwan-senpai told her. “Yes, Tianyu-san. Your cheeks are gaunt. Have you been eating properly?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. I’ve had food from Court Physician Liu’s place.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu, thinking that he couldn’t let Tianyu run loose, took on the responsibility to feed him, but as expected, he was impossible to tame.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even Maomao knew very well that agitating Tianyu would be difficult. Which is why she used a special tool.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so?” Maomao took out a large basket. Inside the basket was…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“M-my word!&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A large chicken. It has been decapitated, feathers plucked and blood drained. It was a spent hen that couldn’t lay eggs anymore, not a young chicken, but that was why it would have good flavour. It would be very delicious simmered well into a thick soup with an addition of egg and kudzu powder.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao, who often went into town for work, had been entrusted with buying supper as well. If she made soup in the medical office and brought it back, the court physicians would be grateful to her and she would also save on dinner expenses–one stone two birds.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, it wasn’t the soup that Tianyu was jumping at.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahhhh, I beg you. Please, Niangniang. Can’t you let me dismantle that chicken?” Hands dramatically on his cheeks, his normally dull fish-like eyes were sparkling.　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu understood. A pay cut alone wouldn’t make Tianyu repent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The thing that would distress this guy would be…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Not letting Tianyu do his favourite dissections.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He messed up on the surgery, so for the time being, he was banned from surgeries. Not only that, he wasn’t allowed to dissect dead bodies or dismantle animals.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He had no money, so he couldn’t buy meat from the markets either.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Occasionally, when his withdrawal symptoms arose, they would just give him a bullfrog.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahhh, I beg you. I&amp;#8217;ll process it well, so let me dismantle iiit.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No way.” Normally, she would save time and let him do it, but today she will continue to tease him. “Ahhh, come to think of it. I need water. I’ll have to fill up this water jug.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, I’ll do it for you. Please, I beg youuu.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After teasing him, he drew water and did the laundry for her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As work finished early, Maomao did side jobs in the medical office. Yo did the same. She sat down next to Maomao and rolled up the washed bandages.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the next room, Tianyu, who had finally acquired the chicken to dismantle, displayed his magnificent knife skills. He followed the muscle and divided it up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ll be using the thigh meat for stir-fry, so please cut it into bite-sized pieces. Please boil the bones in the pot together with spring onion.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Okaaay.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao will do the seasoning. Her colleague En’en was better at cooking, but she wasn’t here today, so it can’t be helped.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is this fine? Didn’t Court Physician Liu put a stop to it?” Yo whispered to Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you don’t give him bait once in a while, he would try to dismantle a nearby person sooner or later, wouldn&amp;#8217;t he?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;There’s no way.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;No, he will.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tianyu was this dangerous. Hence why you need to know how to take control of his reins.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please remove the scum properly,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Got it,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While such an exchange occurred, the old court physician showed up. “Oh, what is today’s supper?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s egg drop soup,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh hoh. You want wood ear mushroom?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please give me if you have.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The old court physician took out a dried black item from the medicine box. This shrewd court physician purchased herbal medicine that can be used as condiments or ingredients. His excuse was that maintaining the health of court physicians was also a splendid job.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While Maomao reconstituted the wood ear in hot water, she added wine and salt and then seasoned it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The chicken stir-fry was haphazardly made with whatever vegetable was available.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Court Physician-sama. Can we cultivate a field?” Maomao asked the old court physician.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao wanted to cook with freshly picked herbs like green spring onions and garlic chives. And if possible, she also wanted to grow a lot of herbal medicines.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No can do. There was a case before where a court lady who had been entrusted to manage the field made a blunder.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’re right,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He was talking about Suirei. Having plotted Jinshi’s assassination, she was now not allowed to exist.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As the old court physician’s nose twitched, he read a note.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The child over there is Yo, correct?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;hm, can you come over for a moment?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is it?” Yo asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He showed Yo, not Maomao, the journal. Curious, Maomao also came over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The note was from a court physician working in another region.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;This is.” Yo’s complexion changed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, things might be getting a little scary.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the note, it was written that there has been an increase in patients who were breaking out in blisters.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: People have been asking about what Tianyu did during the surgery. The details are in LN15, but essentially, he refused to do his job when it was his time to step up.&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-02-chitchat/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-01-chicken-meat/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4935-6767064ca5ce3' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241221#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4935&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4935-6767064ca5ce3' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4935-6767064ca5ce3' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-01-chicken-meat/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
